  "text": "Data. The research was carried out in Abia State in southeast Nigeria as part of the study of NCDs in the state. A survey emphasizing NCDs and their risk factors was conducted between August 2011 and April 2012. The estimated population of the state as of 2015 was 3,601,916, based on the 2006 population and an annual estimated growth rate of 2.8%. [CITATION_1] The study population consisted of all individuals aged 18 years and above, who had been a resident in the state for at least six months prior to the time of the survey.",
